(Electrical)
Importance: High

 

Hi Felix

 

Upon submitting the fee, client had further clarified on the required scope
of work more in detail and are described below:

 

1.	Electrical feeds to the guard huts, street lights, washdown bay and
associated hydraulic services as part of electrical 

*	The electrical requirements are written with green annotations in
the drawings.
*	The streetlights are on Defence property, so no ASP Level 3 designs
required. All electrical work is on Defence property.
*	The hydraulic services themselves are not part of your scope, only
the power supply. 

2.	Relocation of existing streetlights and subsequent power
reticulation
3.	Power reticulation to other services including hydraulic
4.	Maximum demand calculations for new additional loads
5.	Review of existing infrastructure (switchboards etc) to ensure
compatibility and capacity
6.	Please consider an allowance for 1 site inspection to familiarise
the existing site conditions, as a separate price (if required)

 

Can you please review and provide your revised fee proposal accordingly.

Could you please review the provided documents again with this knowledge in
mind, and come back to me with a revised proposal?

Also, could you please confirm the value of your Professional Indemnity and
Public Liability Insurance policies?

 

Best Regards

Hi Felix

 

We are dealing with a D&C contractor to demolish the existing guard huts and
replace them with pre-fabricated guard huts at the Beecroft Weapons Range,
Jervis Bay.

The required scope of work is to provide only the Electrical feed to these
prefabricated huts (no internal electrical design for the huts are
required).

I have attached the full set of drawings for your reference.

 

Can you please review and provide your best offer for the electrical
services by tomorrow afternoon.

 

Note:

The contractor is scheduled to submit the designs in early February and
expects us to complete the scope and send through for review by Friday 3rd
February 2024.

Please let me know if you can accommodate within this timeframe and provide
a priced proposal.

 



 

Best Regards
